@martinwicke  Thanks for confirming that tensorflow does not need tensorboard, and that the dependency is in fact technically the other way around.

> It's relatively free in terms of dependencies

This is incorrect. Tensorflow depends on 7 packages. Tensorboard depends on 5 more packages ---  some of which are old (unmaintained?) versions. Bleach 1.5.0 is not compatible with python 3.6. Until https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorboard/issues/588 is resolved the Tensorboard  dependency is a burden for those who do not use it.
